(1, 'UI/UX Design', 'ui-ux-design', '1676197400.jpg', '1676197400-png', 'User Interface and User Experience are two new digital design fields that are reshaping the world of app, website, and product design. They have become important factors when it comes to the success of digital products. If your product fails to incorporate these principles, then users will not be able to find the information they need or use your products as effectively as possible. If you’re a potential graphic designer or just looking to build your portfolio with some new skills, learning UI/ UX Designing can open up a world of opportunities for you. With these skills, you can create websites, apps, and more that are clean, intuitive, and enjoyable for your users. It’s a challenging field where even small details can make a big difference in how user-friendly an interface is (and whether people will stay on that site).', '<p>User Interface and User Experience are two new digital design fields that are reshaping the world of app, website, and product design. They have become important factors when it comes to the success of digital products. If your product fails to incorporate these principles, then users will not be able to find the information they need or use your products as effectively as possible. If you&rsquo;re a potential graphic designer or just looking to build your portfolio with some new skills, learning UI/ UX Designing can open up a world of opportunities for you. With these skills, you can create websites, apps, and more that are clean, intuitive, and enjoyable for your users. It&rsquo;s a challenging field where even small details can make a big difference in how user-friendly an interface is (and whether people will stay on that site).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are endless opportunities in the design field, and there are few things as rewarding as knowing that the product you&rsquo;ve created is being used and loved by many people. The demand for designers is only going to increase with time as the internet becomes more and more a part of people&rsquo;s daily lives. Additionally, more and more businesses are making the shift to digital, which means more and more websites and apps will be needed to serve them.</p>\r\n<p>The UI refers to the design and functionality of an app or website&rsquo;s interface that users interact with. It&rsquo;s what you see when you visit a website or app and the design of each page or screen. An interface could be something as simple as a website&rsquo;s homepage or something as complex as a smartphone app. The UX refers to the overall user experience of an app or website. It&rsquo;s how easy a user can navigate through an app or website, how intuitive it is to use, and how pleasant it is to interact with. When it comes to a website or app, UX design is about more than just how an app or website looks.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-02-12 04:38:20', '2023-02-12 04:38:20'),
(2, 'Mobile App Development', 'mobile-app-development', '1676197627.jpg', '1676197627-png', 'Mobile app development is the process of creating applications that are specifically designed for mobile devices. When it comes to mobile app development trends, the industry keeps changing at a fast pace. New ideas, technologies, and innovations are coming out for developers on a regular basis. Even so, some of these changes stay for longer than others. Mobile Application development is the set of procedure that involved in writing software for smartphones and other hand-held devices. The two most prominent mobile platforms are iOS from Apple and Android from Google.', '<p>Mobile app development is the process of creating applications that are specifically designed for mobile devices. When it comes to mobile app development trends, the industry keeps changing at a fast pace. New ideas, technologies, and innovations are coming out for developers on a regular basis. Even so, some of these changes stay for longer than others. Mobile Application development is the set of procedure that involved in writing software for smartphones and other hand-held devices. The two most prominent mobile platforms&nbsp;are iOS from Apple and Android from Google.</p>\r\n<p>The mobile development process involves creating installable software bundles implementing&nbsp;back end services such as data access with an API, and testing the application on target devices. There are four major development approaches when building mobile applications and they are: native mobile applications, cross-platform native mobile applications, hybrid mobile applications, progressive web applications. Each of these approaches has their own way for developing mobile applications and also has certain advantages and disadvantages. Native mobile applications uses the framework provided by the platform owner and runs directly on the operating system of the device such as IOS and Android. Cross-platform native mobile applications can be written in variety of different programming languages and frameworks. They are compiled into a native application running directly on the operating system of the device.&nbsp; Hybrid mobile applications are built with standard web technologies. &nbsp;Whereas, Progressive web application offer an alternative approach to traditional mobile app development by skipping app store delivery and app installations. PWAs are web applications that utilize a set of browser capabilities such as working offline, running a background process and so on. There are hundreds of cloud and 3rd party services that mobile application developers can leverage to speed up the development and delivery of their applications.</p>\r\n<p>Designing a mobile app is no different from designing an experience for any other screen. The main difference is the user interface(UI). In a desktop world, touchscreens may not exist for every user. But when you&rsquo;re designing for mobile devices, the experience is only for touchscreens. Likewise, in a desktop environment, cameras and location information may not be readily available, but on a mobile device these elements are everywhere.</p>', '2023-02-12 04:42:07', '2023-02-12 04:42:07'),
(3, 'Web Development', 'web-development', '1676197738.jpg', '1676197738-png', 'Web development, in general, refers to the tasks associated with creating websites for hosting on an intranet or the internet. Web design, web content development, client-side/server-side scripting, and network security configuration are all part of the web development process. Web development, in a broad sense, refers to all of the actions, updates, and operations required to build, maintain, and manage a website to ensure optimal performance, user experience, and speed.', '<p>Web development, in general, refers to the tasks associated with creating websites for hosting on an intranet or the internet. Web design, web content development, client-side/server-side scripting, and network security configuration are all part of the web development process. Web development, in a broad sense, refers to all of the actions, updates, and operations required to build, maintain, and manage a website to ensure optimal performance, user experience, and speed.</p>\r\n<p>Web development is also known as website development. The professionals that maintain a website are called web developers or (more commonly) web&nbsp;devs. Web development is the process of coding or programming that enables website functionality based on the needs of the owner. It primarily addresses the non-design aspects of website development, such as coding and markup. Web development encompasses everything from simple text pages to complex web-based applications, social network apps, and electronic business applications. The following is the web development hierarchy: Client-side programming, Server-side programming, Database engineering. To create websites, most web developers use Hypertext Markup Language (HTML), Cascading Style Sheets (CSS), and JavaScript.</p>\r\n<p>HTML defines a website\'s basic framework - the foundation upon which everything else is built. It creates the blocks that define the layout, format, and critical components of a page. Although it is theoretically possible to code a website entirely in HTML, it will be a bare bones site with no functions unless enhanced with CSS and JavaScript. Furthermore, even simple style changes, such as changing the color of a button, necessitate a significant amount of coding when done solely with HTML. CSS is used to style the content of a website by utilizing a small set of files that are shared throughout the site. This way, whenever a change needs to be made, such as changing the color of all the buttons on every page of the website, a web developer only needs to edit a single CSS file.&nbsp;The JavaScript programming language is used to manage the interactivity of numerous distinct website elements. It can be used to make effects that change the look of icons and drop-down menus, as well as to add animations, games, and other interactive elements.</p>\r\n<p>Front-end developers, back-end developers, and full-stack developers are the three types of web developers. A front-end developer is responsible for all visual aspects of the website (layout, navigation bar, etc.), as well as its interactivity and tying all of its elements together. Back-end developers manage the website\'s hosting services, database, and applications, among other things, to ensure that it runs smoothly. Back-end developers may need to use additional server-side languages such as Python, Ruby, Java, and PHP to solve server issues.</p>', '2023-02-12 04:43:58', '2023-02-12 04:43:58'),
(4, 'Digital Marketing', 'digital-marketing', '1676197828.jpg', '1676197828-png', 'Social media marketing is the practice of increasing website traffic and brand recognition through online interaction. You may promote your business, goods, services, culture, and more via social media marketing. Concentrating on social media marketing can be beneficial because billions of people use social media platforms to interact.', '<p>Any form of marketing that can be measured by marketing experts across the consumer journey and that leverages electronic devices to deliver promotional messaging. Digital marketing is most commonly used to describe advertising campaigns that run on a computer, phone, tablet, or other electronic device. Online video, display ads, search engine marketing, paid social ads, and social media posts are just a few examples of the various formats it can take. Digital marketing is frequently contrasted with \"conventional marketing\" methods like direct mail, billboards, and magazine advertisements. Oddly, traditional marketing is frequently grouped with television.</p>\r\n<p>The promotion of brands via the internet and other digital communication channels is known as digital marketing, sometimes known as online marketing. This comprises text and multimedia messages as well as email, social media, and web-based advertising as a marketing channel.</p>\r\n<p>Social media marketing is the practice of increasing website traffic and brand recognition through online interaction. You may promote your business, goods, services, culture, and more via social media marketing. Concentrating on social media marketing can be beneficial because billions of people use social media platforms to interact.</p>\r\n<p>Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram are the most widely used digital channels for social media marketing, followed closely by LinkedIn and YouTube. The social media channels you use for your business ultimately depend on your objectives and target market. For instance, targeting your audience on LinkedIn is a fantastic idea if you want to get new leads for your&nbsp; firm because professionals in the field are active there. However, posting advertisements on social media ads on Instagram/Facebook may be better for your brand if you run a B2C focused on younger consumers.</p>\r\n<p>Social media marketing is a type of digital marketing that makes use of the strength of well-known social media platforms to meet your branding and marketing objectives. However, it goes beyond simply setting up company accounts and posting whenever you feel like it. A dynamic approach with quantifiable objectives is needed for social media marketing and includes:</p>\r\n<p>-Preserving and improving your profiles.</p>\r\n<p>-Posting content that promotes your company and draws in the right audience, such as images,&nbsp;&nbsp; videos, tales, and live videos.</p>\r\n<p>-Addressing remarks, shares, and likes while keeping an eye on your reputation.</p>\r\n<p>-To create a brand community, follow and interact with your followers, clients, and influencers.</p>\r\n<p>Paid social media advertising is another form of social media marketing where you can pay to get individuals that are specifically interested in your business see your brand.</p>', '2023-02-12 04:45:28', '2023-02-12 04:45:28'),
(5, 'Custom Software Development', 'custom-software-development', '1676197993.jpg', '1676197993-png', 'The main advantage of custom software is that you alone own the one-of-a-kind solution. Instead of waiting for updates, you may make changes whenever you want. You can include fresh material, incorporate client comments, and more. This will enhance your clients\' user experience and foster a more interactive relationship with them.', '<p>The process of creating software applications is known as custom software development. These software solutions were created for certain users, processes, and business needs. To put it simply, it is just regular software development with a specific target audience and intended application in mind. As a result, it is also referred to as bespoke software.</p>\r\n<p>A website builder is a nice example. Programmers build a customized website that meets the client\'s needs rather than charging thousands of dollars for a generic web page design.</p>\r\n<p>Custom application development approaches regularly improved throughout time. To create reliable and high-quality applications, people began to create new scientific methodologies. Software solutions finally took off like a rocket, despite the fact that it took a long time for them to first satisfy the client\'s need. Thousands of businesses currently create dynamic, lightweight websites to meet the needs of their customers.</p>\r\n<p>Custom software development is the process of making a specially designed application for any person or business. But it\'s not just about developing it; it also need ongoing maintenance throughout time.</p>\r\n<p>Why is custom software development necessary?</p>\r\n<p>To fulfill sophisticated plans that a pre-made can\'t meet, custom software is crucial. It enables business owners of products to understand their thought processes and generate revenue.</p>\r\n<p>The creation of custom software offers time and money-saving options. It aids in cost-cutting and increases production. They also offer a larger variety of capabilities than traditional applications. The emphasis on customization draws attention to the special design elements that let your users modify the program to suit their own particular requirements.</p>\r\n<p>The main advantage of custom software is that you alone own the one-of-a-kind solution. Instead of waiting for updates, you may make changes whenever you want. You can include fresh material, incorporate client comments, and more. This will enhance your clients\' user experience and foster a more interactive relationship with them.</p>\r\n<p>At Aasha Tech, we have a team of highly qualified specialists who have consistently provided our clients with the greatest outcomes. Our programmers and other experts have experience in project management, QA testing, and UI/UX design, among other software development services.</p>', '2023-02-12 04:48:13', '2023-02-12 04:48:13'),
(6, 'Graphic Design', 'graphic-design', '1676198106.jpg', '1676198106-png', 'With the ongoing digitization of our world today, the design process has advanced significantly. But even though these procedures have evolved over time, designers continue to employ classic graphic design materials like pencil and paper.\r\n\r\nThe majority of graphic artists employ a hybrid workflow that combines analog and digital tools. Designers frequently begin the design process by roughing out ideas with conventional graphic design tools before launching into the computer for finalization. By allowing designers to explore ideas and produce designs more rapidly rather than having to do everything by hand, technologies have improved the creative process.', '<p>Graphic design is the practice of using words, pictures, and other visual elements to communicate ideas to an audience, often in order to achieve a certain result. To put it another way, graphic design is communication design; it is a means of expressing ideas through imagery and style.</p>\r\n<p>With the ongoing digitization of our world today, the design process has advanced significantly. But even though these procedures have evolved over time, designers continue to employ classic graphic design materials like pencil and paper.</p>\r\n<p>The majority of graphic artists employ a hybrid workflow that combines analog and digital tools. Designers frequently begin the design process by roughing out ideas with conventional graphic design tools before launching into the computer for finalization. By allowing designers to explore ideas and produce designs more rapidly rather than having to do everything by hand, technologies have improved the creative process.</p>\r\n<p>Graphic designers are essentially visual communicators, which is another name for graphic design, or communication design. Through the most popular graphic design software, they bring visual thoughts to life and use text, graphics, and images to engage or inform consumers.</p>\r\n<p>One method for businesses to engage their customers is through graphic design. It is possible to utilize design to market and sell goods, to spread a message, or to create a distinctive brand identity. Graphic designers blend art and business, therefore the creative process is influenced by business objectives even while some graphic design has a commercial aim.</p>\r\n<p>The creation of visually appealing goods that convey specific messages or information is the aim of graphic design. Our graphic designers concentrate on design composition principles, typography, layout, and branding. They work on a variety of projects, including logo design, packaging, animation, and flyers.</p>', '2023-02-12 04:50:06', '2023-02-12 04:50:06');

